2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper discusses the overestimation bias problem in Q-learning and proposes a new algorithm to mitigate it, which is a common problem in reinforcement learning and falls under the umbrella of AI. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of control theory and falls under the category of systems and control. 
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems): The paper discusses the performance of Q-learning in different environments, which can be related to multiagent systems where the performance of an agent depends on the behavior of other agents. 
5. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper proposes a new algorithm for Q-learning, which can be applied to robotics applications where reinforcement learning is commonly used.
